Document: PhysicsServer3DRenderingServerHandler  
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsserver3drenderingserverhandler.rst  
Summary: Methods for setting bounding boxes, normals, and vertex positions on SoftBody3D objects via the PhysicsServer3D.  

Method: _set_aabb(AABB: AABB) → void  
Called by PhysicsServer3D to set the bounding box for SoftBody3D.  

Method: _set_normal(vertex_id: int, normal: Vector3) → void  
Called by PhysicsServer3D to set the normal for SoftBody3D vertex at index vertex_id. Note: The normal parameter used to be of type const void* prior to Godot 4.2.  

Method: _set_vertex(vertex_id: int, vertex: Vector3) → void  
Called by PhysicsServer3D to set the position for SoftBody3D vertex at index vertex_id. Note: The vertex parameter used to be of type const void* prior to Godot 4.2.  

Method: set_aabb(AABB: AABB) → void  
Sets the bounding box for SoftBody3D.  

Method: set_normal(vertex_id: int, normal: Vector3) → void  
Sets the normal for SoftBody3D vertex at index vertex_id.  

Method: set_vertex(vertex_id: int, vertex: Vector3) → void  
Sets the position for SoftBody3D vertex at index vertex_id.